content:
Before you set up Unified Knowledge, review its limitations. Unified Knowledge is available in Lightning Experience and Unlimited Edition with the Knowledge add-on license.

Read-only Articles, Deletion, and Video Limitations:
- Third-party knowledge that is imported and synced in Salesforce is read-only.
- You can’t use the Salesforce user interface to delete individual, third-party knowledge articles stored in Salesforce.
- Videos are only embedded from approved Salesforce video sites.

Article Display and Rendering Limitations:
- Non-image links from third-party articles display as text when imported or synced into articles in Salesforce.
- In the Salesforce mobile app and the Safari browser on iPads, only the first page of PDFs displays.
- In the Salesforce mobile app for Android, you’re asked to download PDFs.

Knowledge and Storage Limitations:
- Third-party knowledge counts towards your org’s Knowledge limits and overall storage limits.
- The default org limit for articles is 50,000. To increase limits, log a case with Salesforce Customer Support.

Article Character Limitations:
- A maximum of 131,000 characters is allowed on each article when importing and converting third-party sources to HTML.

Einstein Service Replies for Email Limitations:
- Einstein-generated emails are grounded only on the first 2,661 characters of third-party articles synced with Unified Knowledge.
title: Service Cloud Unified Knowledge Limitations
